  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.content.ComponentCallbacks, android.content.ComponentCallbacks2
    public abstract class SubscriptionsService extends android.app.IntentService
    Service that is started when Virtuoso syncs with the Backplane's subscription services - this may happen in response to a Push notification or during the course of a normal sync. If you override onHandleIntent, you must ensure that onHandleIntent is called in the super class. This method processes any episodic content that has been updated on the server. Clients must provide their own implementation of the SubscriptionsService, the default behavior inherited from SubscriptionsService is to simply process the data sent down from the Backplane and prepare an asset for download.

    There are 3 rules which affect subscriptions:
    • Maximum number of assets: defines the maximum number of assets which should be stored for the feed (defaults to Integer.MAX_VALUE).
    • Auto deletion of old episodes: defines whether old assets can be automatically deleted to make room for new ones once the Maximum number of assets has been met (defaults to true).
    • Maximum bit rate: defines the maximum bit rate that should be used when choosing a profile for segmented HLS files (defaults to -1 i.e. best rate available).
    The global defaults for these rules can be configured through the Virtuoso API's: setMaxAssetsForSubscriptions, setCanAutoDeleteForSubscriptions, setMaxBitrateForSubscriptions
    The above rules can also be configured on a per feed basis using the Virtuoso API's: setFeedMaxAssets, setFeedCanDelete, setFeedMaxBitRate or whilst the SubscriptionsService is processing the feed data.

    The SubscriptionsService will not add any additional metadata to an item, It will use the default values for Expiry After Play and Expiry After Download - as provided from the Backplane.

    Client applications have the opportunity to modify the item or feed which is being created and/or create their own internal mappings by overriding the processingFeedWithData, processingAssetWithData, processedAsset, willAddAssetToQueue methods.
    These methods are called as follows:
    1. processingFeedWithData: Called when the SubscriptionsService is processing the Feed data sent down from the Backplane. It is here that client applications have the opportunity to modify the rules on a per feed basis.
    2. processingAssetWithData: Called when the SubscriptionsService is processing an Asset from a Feed, client applications have the opportunity to modify the default values and intercept any additional data they need for their UI e.g. getting a thumbnail url.
    3. processedAsset: Called once an Asset has successfully been processed. At this point the item has not yet been added to the download queue.
    4. willAddAssetToQueue: Called just before the asset is added to the download Queue, an asset is only added if the rules for the feed permit the addition - Client applications will receive a callback in the Engine Observer once the asset has been successfully added to the queue.

      processedAsset 
      void processedAsset(IIdentifier aIdentifier)
      Called once the subscription data has been processed successfully.
      public void processedAsset(IIdentifier aIdentifier)
      Called once the subscription data has been processed successfully. The call occurs after processingAssetWithData. At the time of this call the Asset will not yet have been added to the download queue it is in a deferred state, it will remain in that state until it can be added to the queue. Before the Asset is added to the queue a call to willAddAssetToQueue will occur. willAddAssetToQueue will only occur if the rule for maximum number of Assets in the feed has not yet been satisfied or if the auto deletion rule has been set.
      Parameters:
      aIdentifier - The asset which has been processed.
      processingAssetWithData 
      org.json.JSONObject processingAssetWithData(java.lang.String uuid, org.json.JSONObject data, boolean complete)
      Method is called prior to create an asset in Virtuoso.
      public org.json.JSONObject processingAssetWithData(java.lang.String uuid, org.json.JSONObject data, boolean complete)
      Method is called prior to create an asset in Virtuoso. If complete is false, applications must supply any missing mandatory fields.
      Clients add fields to the JSONObject using one of the keys specified in SubscriptionKey
      The Mandatory fields for adding an asset are:
      • SubscriptionKey.ASSET_TYPE : sets the type of asset that should be created (i.e HLS or Flat)
      • SubscriptionKey.ASSET_ID : The UUID of the asset.
      • SubscriptionKey.DOWNLOAD_URL : The Url of where the content is downloaded from.
      • SubscriptionKey.COLLECTION_ID : The ID of the feed the asset belongs to.

      In addition to the mandatory fields clients can provide additional data for creating the item. In order to add optional fields clients will need to either access their catalog directly or use other meta data that has been sent with the subscription information. e.g: 
       
   public JSONObject processingAssetWithData(String uuid, JSONObject data, boolean complete){

       //checking of mandatory fields if needed ...

       //adding optional meta data
       if(data.has(SubscriptionsKey.META_DATA)){
           JSONObject metaData = data.getJSONObject(SubscriptionsKey.META_DATA);
           String title = metaData.optString("title")
           if(!TextUtils.isEmpty(title)){
               data.put(SubscriptionsKey.ASSET_META_DATA,"{title:"+title+"}");
           }
       }
       return data;
   }
      Parameters:
      uuid - The UUID of the asset being created
      data - Data used to create the asset
      complete - True, all mandatory data is present
      Returns:
      Data used to create the asset
      See Also:
      SubscriptionKey
      processingFeedWithData 
      org.json.JSONObject processingFeedWithData(java.lang.String uuid, org.json.JSONObject data, boolean complete)
      Method is called prior to creating a feed in the database.
      public org.json.JSONObject processingFeedWithData(java.lang.String uuid, org.json.JSONObject data, boolean complete)
      Method is called prior to creating a feed in the database. This allows clients to set the values to be used for the feeds settings. Clients can set the values for:
      • Maximum number of items allowed in a feed
      • Auto deletion of old items
      • Maximum bit rate to be used when downloading HLS items
      Clients add the value to the JSONObject using one of the keys specified in SubscriptionKey
      e.g: 
       
   public JSONObject processingFeedWithData(String uuid, JSONObject data, boolean complete){
       data.put(SubscriptionsKey.FEED_CAN_DELETE,true);
       return data;
   }
      Parameters:
      uuid - The UUID of the feed
      data - The data for the feed
      complete - When true, the feed has all required information
      Returns:
      The JSONObject to create the feed with.
      See Also:
      SubscriptionKey.FEED_CAN_DELETE, SubscriptionKey.FEED_MAX_ITEMS, SubscriptionKey.MAX_BIT_RATE
